docking
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:the removal of lambs tails with either knife, searing iron or rubber ring. [Used mainly in the N.I.and is used loosely to include ear-marking and castration of male lambs.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:tailing
